Still basking in the euphoria of the success of his last body of work, fast-rising musical act, Ajani Fahad Oladimeji aka Addicto has stated he is enjoying the attention his been attracting following the release of his much-talked about EP “Cloth Matter.” According to the singing sensation, since the release of his EP, his fame has shot up and he’s relishing every bit of attention coming his way. In a recent post on his social media handle, Addicto opened up on his early life, how far he has come with music while hunting on releasing another song soon.   N’ Delta ministry, NDDC held by ‘Abuja…     Makinde approves recruitment of fresh 500 Amotekun…     Ondo Assembly to review Amotekun law to tackle rising…   He said: “Music has been a thing I grew up with. It’s in the blood and I think I am gradually making it happen and my parents are happy for me. Although it has not been an easy journey but one has to forge on and get it done no matter what.” Speaking about his latest four-track EP (extended play), titled “Cloth Matter”, with songs such as File, Origin, and others, he confessed he least expected the level of love shown him by his fans yet again. “I am still amazed at the massive turnout and I can’t appreciate my fans enough. They have continued to throw their weight behind me since day one and I promise not to disappoint them. Soon, I will be coming with a new banger to delight them,” the singer added.